citation.case_name: Interstate Investors, Inc. v. United States

html:
393 U.S. 479

89 S.Ct. 707

21 L.Ed.2d 687

INTERSTATE INVESTORS, INC.
v.
UNITED STATES et al.

No. 755.

Supreme Court of the United States

January 27, 1969

Frederick W. P. Lorenzen and William R. Burt, for appellant.

Solicitor General Griswold, Assistant Attorney General Zimmerman, Howard E. Shapiro, Robert W. Ginnane and Jerome Nelson, for the United States and others.

Thomas F. Daly, John W. Castles III, and Warren A. Goff, for appellee Tran continental Bus System.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motions to affirm are granted and the judgment is affirmed.
